works.description: We have seen plenty of gold plated Nokia handsets, but the latest one comes from the house of Nokia itself. A great option for those who can’t afford a Vertu version, the new Nokia Oro features 18-carat gold plating, a sapphire crystal and leather from one of Scotland’s finest Caledonian herds. The Oro (meaning “Gold” in Italian) handset is basically the Symbian-based Nokia C7, which has been given the gilded treatment.
